    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed the required level. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is accepted because ASTM F1717 prescribes a single standard test configuration for regulatory submissions and no clinically relevant alternative loading conditions exist within the standard's scope. All quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval < 1.96, QoI difference < 10%) are satisfied for all three quantities of interest. The FEA model ensemble is deemed credible for supporting the regulatory submission decision.",
